# Hardware Details

## Components Used
- Arduino Uno
- DHT11 Temperature Sensor
- Voltage Sensor Module
- Current Sensor (ACS712)
- Relay Module (Fan control)
- 16x2 LCD Display
- Buzzer
- LED
- Resistors & Capacitors

## Connections
- DHT11 → Digital Pin 2
- Voltage Sensor → A0
- Current Sensor → A1
- Relay → Pin 7
- Buzzer → Pin 8
- LED → Pin 9
- LCD → Pins (12, 11, 5, 4, 3, 6)

## Working Setup
Sensors continuously monitor battery parameters and send data to Arduino, which processes and controls outputs.
